commit.message: Add github actions to test building

Windows: depend on WIN32 package, implement and export hSize

WIN32 supports getConsoleScreenBufferInfo since version 2.6.2.0 and
withHandleToHANDLE that supports console handles since 2.13.2.0.

The fallback for Cygwin or MSYS shells now passes the given handle to
the std_in of the "stty size" command. Since size is now implemented as
`hSize stdout`, it works correctly even if stdin is redirected.

Drop #let directive, which is a built-in.

#alignment is a hsc2hs builtin.

posix: Fix ioctl foreign import

Previously the type of the `request` argument of `ioctl`'s
`foreign import` was incorrect. This can result in incorrect
code generation (and subsequent unsoundness) on some platforms.
Moreover, the import used the `ccall` calling convention, which can
break in surprising ways on platforms which play tricks with CPP.

Move stderr of stty to pipe

If stderr is left as its default value, any error messages arising from
stty are output to the stderr of the program calling `size`, causing
strange messages if stty fails.
Add GHC 7.10 and 8.0 to the test matrix.
Add ghc-prim dependency for GHC 7.2, compiling on that version then works.

Derive more instances

  - Add `Typeable Window` and `Data Window` on all supported GHC
    versions.

  - Add `Generic Window` on GHC >= 7.2.

  - Add `Generic1 Window` on GHC >= 7.6.

  - Use `-XDerive{Foldable,Functor,Traversable}` to define
    `{Foldable,Functor,Traversable} Window` (they're supported since at
    least GHC 7.0).
Version bump, fixed distribution, nix boilerplate, travis update
Switch to the right Fd import
Fix typo in the module name
Split the Size module up into three, so the cross-platform bit is separate
